$$
s_{i}^{(t)}=\left\{\frac{\mathbb{P}_{\mathcal{M}_{t}}(\hat{y}_{i}^{(t)}|\mathbf{x}_{i})}{\sum_{a\in A_{i}}\mathbb{P}_{\mathcal{M}_{t}}(a|\mathbf{x}_{i})}\right.\,\,\,\mathrm{if}\quad\hat{y}_{i}^{(t)}=y_{i}
$$

Input: training set $\mathcal{D}_{\mathrm{train}}$ , LLMs $\{\mathcal{M}_{t}:t=1,\ldots,T\}$ , #positive LLMs $K_{+}$ , #negative LLMs $K_{-}$ , #out-group queries $H$ , #clusters $N$ , hyper-parameter $\lambda$ , mini-batch size $b$ , and learning rate $\eta$ ; learnable parameters $\pmb{\theta}$ : encoder $\mathcal{E}(\cdot;\mathbf{w})$ and LLM embeddings $\{\mathbf{k}_{t}:t=1,\ldots,T\}$ ;   
training:   
1: score LLMs for each sample $(\mathbf{x}_{i},y_{i})\in\mathcal{D}_{\mathrm{train}}$ and obtain {si(t) : t = 1, . . . , T};   
2: cluster training queries $\{\mathbf{x}_{i}:i=1,\ldots,n\}$ into $N$ groups;   
3: repeat   
4: sample a mini-batch of data $\boldsymbol{\mathrm{\Delta}}\boldsymbol{\mathrm{\Omega}}^{\beta}$ from $\mathcal{D}_{\mathrm{train}}$ ;   
5: for $\bar{(}\mathbf{x}_{i},y_{i})\in B$ do   
6: obtain positive LLMs index set $\mathcal{T}_{i}^{+}$ and negative LLMs index set $\mathcal{T}_{i}^{-}$ ;   
7: compute the sample-LLM contrastive loss $\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{sample-LLM}}(\mathbf{x}_{i},y_{i};\pmb{\theta})$ by Eq. (4);   
8: sample an in-group query $\mathbf{x}_{i}^{+}$ and a set of $H$ out-group queries $\mathbf{\mathcal{X}}_{i}^{-}$ from $\boldsymbol{\mathrm{\Delta}}\boldsymbol{\mathrm{\Omega}}_{\boldsymbol{B}}$ ;   
9: compute the sample-sample contrastive loss $\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{sample-sample}}(\mathbf{x}_{i};\pmb{\theta})$ by Eq. (5);   
10: end for   
11: $\begin{array}{r}{\mathcal{L}(\boldsymbol{\mathcal{B}};\boldsymbol{\theta})=\sum_{(\mathbf{x}_{i},y_{i})\in\mathcal{B}}\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{sample-LLM}}(\mathbf{x}_{i},y_{i};\boldsymbol{\theta})+\lambda\;\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{sample-sample}}(\mathbf{x}_{i};\boldsymbol{\theta});}\end{array}$   
12: $\pmb\theta\leftarrow\pmb\theta-\eta\nabla_{\pmb\theta}\mathcal{L}(\mathcal{B};\pmb\theta)$ ;   
13: until converged.   
inference:   
14: sample a testing query $\mathbf{x}^{\prime}$ ;   
15: $t^{\prime}=\arg\operatorname*{max}_{t\in\{1,...,T\}}$ sim(E(x′; w), kt);   
16: $\hat{\mathbf{y}}^{\prime}=\mathcal{M}_{t^{\prime}}(\mathbf{x}^{\prime})$ .

$$
\begin{array}{r}{\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{sample-sample}}(\mathbf{x}_{i};\pmb{\theta})=-\log\frac{e^{\sin(\mathcal{E}(\mathbf{x}_{i};\mathbf{w}),\mathcal{E}(\mathbf{x}_{i}^{+};\mathbf{w}))}}{e^{\sin(\mathcal{E}(\mathbf{x}_{i};\mathbf{w}),\mathcal{E}(\mathbf{x}_{i}^{+};\mathbf{w}))}+\sum_{\mathbf{x}_{i}^{-}\in\mathcal{X}_{i}^{-}}e^{\sin(\mathcal{E}(\mathbf{x}_{i};\mathbf{w}),\mathcal{E}(\mathbf{x}_{i}^{-};\mathbf{w}))}}.}\end{array}
$$
